<br>
1st point cost 2 AA, it gives 2% chance to crit and that crit is only for a small increase.  (best SoFB I have seen with focus bracer was 1480)<br>
<br>
2nd point cost 4 AA, it gives 4% chance to crit and that crit is a smaller increase.  (I got a crit for 1805 last night with SoFB and focus bracer)<br>
<br>
3rd point cost 6 AA, it gives 7% chance to crit.  I believe this crit is for 2x normal nuke.  So I think that will be 1005x2 = 2010 for unfocused SoFB, and like 2408 for a focused SoFB.<br>
<br>
Nobody ever seems to mention the damage scales up along with the chance to crit. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ualladdim.showPublicProfile?language=EN>alladdim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#333333>(10/17/02 6:46:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1594.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: More info...</span><hr size=1> Here's my experience:<br>
